The Committee on Education and Workforce, to whom was re-
ferred the bill (H.R. 1048) to amend the Higher Education Act of
1965 to strengthen disclosure requirements relating to foreign gifts
and contracts, to prohibit contracts between institutions of higher
education and certain foreign entities and countries of concern, and
for other purposes, having considered the same, reports favorably
thereon with an amendment and recommends that the bill as
amended do pass.
The amendment is as follows:
Strike all after the enacting clause and insert the following:
SECTION 1. SHORT TITLE.
This Act may be cited as the ‘‘Defending Education Transparency and Ending
Rogue Regimes Engaging in Nefarious Transactions Act’’ or the ‘‘DETERRENT Act’’.
