tutions. It was voted down along party lines. Democrats also ex-
pressed concern over the Committee’s consideration of H.R. 1048
while DOGE and the Trump Administration have frozen or elimi-
nated funding for billions of dollars in federal research done by in-
stitutions.63 In combination with the chilling effect H.R. 1048
would have on international research, these funding cuts will in-
herently hurt the United States’ ability to conduct scientific re-
search and be competitive in the international economy.
